04:12.043 --> 04:16.378
Multiple small buys of OxyContin, heroin,
cocaine have previously been purchased

04:16.464 --> 04:20.004
from Michael "Studs" Driscoll,
brother of Lanny Driscoll.

04:22.804 --> 04:23.794
Shakespeare.

04:43.450 --> 04:45.066
Hey, Casey, what's up?

04:45.535 --> 04:47.117
I was just thinking about tonight's game.

04:47.621 --> 04:49.237
Give me some numbers. Make 'em good.

04:49.998 --> 04:52.081
What are you talking about,
she got blown up?

04:54.044 --> 04:55.706
Okay, Casey, listen.

04:56.254 --> 04:57.335
Just settle down.

04:57.923 --> 05:00.040
I'm really sorry this happened. I am.

05:00.509 --> 05:01.841
I don't know if Pierce was involved!

05:01.927 --> 05:04.635
I mean, I didn't know she got blown up
till you told me.

05:05.180 --> 05:06.921
Casey, just calm down.

05:07.015 --> 05:09.507
I'm gonna get into it
for you right away, okay?

05:09.935 --> 05:10.925
You all right?

05:11.311 --> 05:15.351
I'll take the over 100 times,
same thing on the parlay.

05:15.440 --> 05:16.521
We'll talk tomorrow.

05:18.527 --> 05:19.483
The fuck was that about?

05:19.945 --> 05:21.186
That was my grandmother.

05:21.279 --> 05:22.736
She misses you. She says, "Hi."

05:22.823 --> 05:23.904
Somebody got blown up?

05:24.783 --> 05:27.196
Just something I'm working on
to pay the bills.

05:27.285 --> 05:29.527
- How much you down?
- How much am I down?

05:30.997 --> 05:32.989
Ask me after tonight's game, okay?

05:33.917 --> 05:35.909
- You ready for this?
- Let's do it.

05:38.171 --> 05:40.003
I was gonna get laid tonight, asshole.

05:40.799 --> 05:42.006
You can still get laid.

05:56.606 --> 05:57.596
Okay.

05:58.608 --> 06:01.396
So, we're two guys
with something they want.

06:02.195 --> 06:03.857
They don't like what we got,

06:03.947 --> 06:05.028
we walk away.

06:06.241 --> 06:08.733
A hundred says that fat fuck
tosses that cigarette

06:08.827 --> 06:11.661
- before we get to the boat.
- Before we step on the boat?

06:11.746 --> 06:12.953
Before we reach the boat.

06:14.624 --> 06:17.116
- You want the bet or not?
- Yeah, fuck it. I'll take it.

06:17.210 --> 06:19.918
Come on, you fat bastard,
toss the cigarette.

06:25.760 --> 06:27.126
What's up, big fella?

06:28.763 --> 06:29.753
How you guys doin'?

06:31.308 --> 06:32.844
Studs, how ya doin'?

06:32.934 --> 06:34.766
That must be Charlie and Danny.

06:35.478 --> 06:36.434
Thank you for coming.

06:37.480 --> 06:39.597
Studs tells me great things
about you guys.

06:39.691 --> 06:41.523
- I appreciate that.
- It's nice to meet you.

06:42.027 --> 06:44.440
- Danny boy.
- Thanks for taking the time.

06:44.529 --> 06:46.361
My brother likes you, I like you.

06:46.698 --> 06:49.782
Danny, why don't you stay with Studs
for a minute. I need to talk to Charlie.

06:51.912 --> 06:53.448
Charlie, come take a look at this boat.

06:54.289 --> 06:56.281
It's a great boat.
It's like a fuckin' hotel.

06:56.625 --> 06:58.992
Picked it up
from a retired dentist in Florida.

06:59.085 --> 07:00.747
Those fuckin' guys are loaded.

07:12.849 --> 07:14.010
Lookin' good, Studs.

07:14.434 --> 07:15.800
You lose a few?

07:16.269 --> 07:18.181
What are you down to now, whale weight?

07:18.271 --> 07:19.387
Go fuck your hand.

07:19.731 --> 07:20.938
I got a thyroid problem.

07:21.441 --> 07:23.148
- Come on. I'm kidding.
- Don't kid.

07:33.328 --> 07:34.990
Who you lookin' at, you fat fuck?

07:35.789 --> 07:36.779
Who you starin' at?

07:42.337 --> 07:43.293
I need a light.

07:54.683 --> 07:55.673
Thanks.

07:56.309 --> 07:57.299
Sure.

08:04.734 --> 08:06.020
Police! Don't you move!

08:06.987 --> 08:08.319
You fuckin' prick!

09:25.815 --> 09:26.646
Danny! It's me!

09:27.358 --> 09:28.269
It's me!

09:28.818 --> 09:29.979
What the fuck happened?

09:30.737 --> 09:32.694
Driscoll! He made us!

09:34.532 --> 09:36.489
- Are you good?
- Find Driscoll!

09:42.123 --> 09:43.113
Oh Jesus...

09:44.292 --> 09:45.282
Charlie!

09:47.295 --> 09:48.536
He's wired, Charlie!

09:49.422 --> 09:50.458
He's a cop!

09:50.548 --> 09:52.039
- What?
- He's a cop!

09:52.467 --> 09:53.878
Are you fucking kidding me?

09:58.181 --> 09:59.217
Charlie!

10:27.836 --> 10:29.543
<i>Drop your weapon!</i>

12:10.021 --> 12:11.182
One time, believe it or not,

12:11.272 --> 12:13.184
there used to be
a whole amusement park here.

12:14.234 --> 12:17.523
Your grandfather used to have
a cigar, cigarette, and tackle shack

12:17.612 --> 12:18.693
over there by the pier.

12:18.780 --> 12:20.237
Where I met your old man.

12:21.491 --> 12:24.279
I would say we were about... 13 years old.

12:25.078 --> 12:26.910
I used to have a little business
selling bait.

12:28.248 --> 12:31.207
One day, two hoods came by,
and they wanted to take my stand.

12:32.418 --> 12:35.126
They kicked the shit out of me.
They took everything.

12:36.339 --> 12:37.705
And I wanted those guys dead.

12:38.341 --> 12:40.207
I wanted that more than anything in life.

12:40.760 --> 12:43.423
I wanted to take my bait knife,
this one right here,

12:44.389 --> 12:46.551
and I wanted to fillet
those sons of bitches.

12:46.975 --> 12:47.965
But your father,

12:48.643 --> 12:51.932
he saw what I was thinking,
and he made me think it through.

12:53.106 --> 12:55.473
He asked me,
"What do you want most in life?"

12:55.566 --> 12:59.105
I said I wanted them dead.
And he says no. He fought me on that.

12:59.195 --> 13:01.482
He said, "What you really want,
is you want your stand back."

13:01.739 --> 13:04.026
So I took his advice
and I moved my stand downriver.

13:04.117 --> 13:06.655
I made more money with that stand
than the first one.

13:07.537 --> 13:10.325
You see what I'm saying?
If it wasn't for your old man,

13:10.415 --> 13:11.826
God knows where I end up.

13:12.542 --> 13:13.532
Maybe dead.

13:14.419 --> 13:15.626
Or maybe worse.

13:16.421 --> 13:18.162
Maybe painted as a bent cop.

13:18.256 --> 13:20.669
Hey, I gotta tell ya, Danny,

13:20.758 --> 13:22.465
I don't think Charlie was painted bent.

13:23.177 --> 13:24.384
I think he was bent.

13:28.933 --> 13:31.266
<i>I think what Charlie loved
most in life was gambling.</i>

13:32.312 --> 13:34.144
And it put him in Driscoll's pocket.

13:34.230 --> 13:35.892
But, fuck it. Doesn't matter what I think.

13:35.982 --> 13:37.393
'Cause Driscoll sat in a courtroom

13:37.483 --> 13:40.351
and told the jury he had his hooks
into you and Charlie.

13:41.070 --> 13:43.187
You got greedy
and pressed him for more money.

13:43.281 --> 13:46.900
The next thing you know, Charlie was dead,
there's a dead narc nobody knew about,

13:46.993 --> 13:48.450
and you're in a fuckin' cell.

13:49.370 --> 13:52.488
- You really believe that, Jimmy?
- I believe what I see and what I hear.

13:52.582 --> 13:55.950
Driscoll had payments and dates
in his books from both you and Charlie.

13:56.794 --> 13:57.875
I never took a nickel.

13:57.962 --> 13:59.794
Well, no, Charlie did
and he kept your end.

13:59.881 --> 14:02.669
- The fuck he did!
- You stuck your head in the sand.

14:02.759 --> 14:05.843
If there's a crime in that,
you've done it, I've done the same.

14:08.806 --> 14:10.263
When's Driscoll up for parole?

14:10.350 --> 14:11.682
Hey, that's not the move.

14:12.185 --> 14:14.643
That is not the move.
The move is go find Kate.

14:14.729 --> 14:16.436
You know they took her joint away?

14:16.522 --> 14:18.980
They trumped up some bullshit,
took her license away,

14:19.067 --> 14:20.148
and closed her down.

14:20.234 --> 14:22.726
- I didn't know that.
- Of course you didn't know that!

14:23.196 --> 14:25.233
Because you're thinking
about something else!

14:30.703 --> 14:31.944
Let me explain something to you.

14:32.038 --> 14:33.870
Every cop in this city hates you,

14:33.956 --> 14:36.323
and they're gonna come after
the thing that you love.

14:36.417 --> 14:38.955
What you need to do is
you need go out and find her.

14:39.045 --> 14:41.002
She's working as a waitress.

14:41.089 --> 14:44.127
As a fucking waitress,
in some joint out in the sticks.

14:44.926 --> 14:45.916
Go find her.

14:46.302 --> 14:48.043
And make a life for yourselves.

14:48.429 --> 14:50.466
Because she's the best thing
that ever happened to you.

14:53.434 --> 14:56.802
Jimmy, I killed Driscoll's brother.
He's not the kind of guy to forget that.

15:05.363 --> 15:07.571
- What do you need from me?
- When's he out?

15:08.533 --> 15:10.274
- Sixth of April.
- Sixth of April?

15:10.493 --> 15:12.405
- He gonna make it?
- Of course he's gonna make it.

15:12.495 --> 15:15.613
He turned in two dirty cops,
the judge thanked him for it.

15:15.706 --> 15:17.823
Sixth of April, he's out,
just like you are.

15:19.001 --> 15:19.991
Now listen to me.

15:20.086 --> 15:22.373
I know you're not bent
like Driscoll said you are,

15:22.463 --> 15:25.547
but if you go kill this guy,
that's exactly what you're gonna be.

15:28.010 --> 15:29.876
Charlie was good, he fooled us both.

15:30.721 --> 15:33.555
But, fuck, it's time to move on.
That's the call here.

15:34.976 --> 15:35.966
Let it go.

15:37.145 --> 15:39.933
Jimmy, if I don't believe in Charlie,
I don't believe in anything.

15:42.859 --> 15:44.020
Welcome home, Danny.

15:47.363 --> 15:48.774
Sorry about the stink.

15:49.449 --> 15:51.987
Been hotter than a dog in heat,
and it ain't even summer yet.

16:06.757 --> 16:09.340
Anything else you need, Danny,
whatever, you let me know.

16:09.427 --> 16:10.508
I owe ya.

16:11.679 --> 16:12.544
Wheels?

16:12.638 --> 16:14.755
Cleaned her up, put a new battery in.

16:16.350 --> 16:17.181
Thanks, Jake.

16:36.579 --> 16:37.569
<i>Hello?</i>

16:39.707 --> 16:41.118
<i>Sorry. One second. Hello?</i>

16:41.751 --> 16:42.741
It's me.

16:45.046 --> 16:46.127
Danny?

16:47.548 --> 16:48.755
I got out.

16:49.717 --> 16:50.878
Yeah, I know.

16:54.472 --> 16:55.713
I've been thinking about you.

16:57.308 --> 16:58.799
<i>Yesterday was your birthday.</i>

17:00.561 --> 17:02.302
<i>Christ, you didn't even remember
your birthday?</i>

17:03.940 --> 17:06.102
I'm sorry they took your place, Kate.

17:07.652 --> 17:09.188
They shouldn't have taken it out on you.

17:10.530 --> 17:11.737
I moved on, Danny.

17:14.242 --> 17:15.483
I'm doing all right.

17:20.039 --> 17:21.029
Look, I have to go.

17:21.499 --> 17:23.536
- Wait, Kate.
<i>- You know what hurts the most?</i>

17:25.545 --> 17:26.626
You cut me off.

17:29.131 --> 17:30.292
Like I was the enemy.

17:32.260 --> 17:33.467
Like I was one of them.

17:34.345 --> 17:35.335
<i>And I wasn't.</i>

17:43.312 --> 17:44.428
I just wanna know why.

17:49.360 --> 17:50.692
<i>I would've waited forever.</i>

17:54.490 --> 17:55.776
<i>Don't call again, Danny.</i>

17:56.576 --> 17:58.033
<i>I don't know what you need.</i>

17:58.536 --> 18:00.198
And I don't know how to fix it.

18:03.082 --> 18:04.368
But I hope you do.

18:38.993 --> 18:40.575
Where you at, Danny boy?

18:40.661 --> 18:42.618
Good till about a minute ago, Milty.

18:43.164 --> 18:44.154
It's Milton.

18:44.540 --> 18:46.247
Assume the position, shithead.

18:47.209 --> 18:48.575
Spread 'em, motherfucker.

18:49.253 --> 18:50.585
I do something wrong?

18:50.671 --> 18:51.582
Jaywalking.

18:51.672 --> 18:52.662
Jaywalking?

18:52.757 --> 18:54.669
You lock jaywalkers up these days?

18:54.759 --> 18:56.125
Only the cop killers.

18:56.636 --> 18:58.593
I'm gonna let you go with a warning
this time.

18:58.846 --> 19:00.508
You ever call me "Milty" again,

19:00.598 --> 19:02.715
I'll put a bullet in your fucking head.

19:50.106 --> 19:51.347
<i>What the fuck happened?</i>

19:51.774 --> 19:52.605
<i>Driscoll!</i>

19:53.067 --> 19:53.932
He made us!

19:57.530 --> 19:58.566
Charlie!

20:08.416 --> 20:10.499
<i>Hey, Casey, what's up?</i>

20:10.584 --> 20:12.120
<i>I was just thinking about tonight's game.</i>

20:12.628 --> 20:14.039
<i>Gimme some numbers, make 'em good.</i>

20:31.105 --> 20:32.346
Casey, this is Gallagher.

20:45.035 --> 20:48.745
Charlie was into me for a lot of money,
so he helped me with my sister.

20:49.290 --> 20:52.203
She was having a problem with her husband.
She found out he was hiding money.

20:53.085 --> 20:54.292
What kind of money?

20:54.378 --> 20:56.244
The kind of money you steal from somebody.

20:56.881 --> 20:59.373
She thought if she could find out
who he was stealing it from,

20:59.467 --> 21:02.050
she could use it against him,
try to save their marriage.

21:02.136 --> 21:03.047
It's nuts.

21:03.137 --> 21:04.628
But that's what she wanted, so...

21:05.264 --> 21:07.881
I made a deal with Charlie
to square up the books,

21:09.059 --> 21:11.142
if she could find what Pierce was up to.

21:12.062 --> 21:13.303
That's her husband, Bill.

21:14.356 --> 21:15.563
Bill Pierce.

21:18.652 --> 21:20.644
So Charlie was tracking Pierce.

21:21.447 --> 21:24.190
Yeah, 'cause I was worried
about my sister, all right?

21:24.283 --> 21:25.364
What'd he find out?

21:25.785 --> 21:27.276
Nothing, as far as I know.

21:27.995 --> 21:31.363
That's why I called Charlie that night.
It was Pierce's car, man, it blew up.

21:32.291 --> 21:33.407
Not Jen's.

21:34.168 --> 21:36.410
Jennifer, that was her name.

21:37.087 --> 21:38.248
What'd the cops say?

21:38.339 --> 21:40.501
They bullshitted around,
made a lot of promises

21:40.591 --> 21:42.674
like they were gonna get who did it,
then nothin'.

21:42.760 --> 21:45.343
- You told them about Pierce?
- A thousand times.

21:45.429 --> 21:48.467
They thought since it was Pierce's car,
he might've been the intended target.

21:48.557 --> 21:49.889
It's fuckin' horseshit.

21:49.975 --> 21:51.932
It's an ongoing investigation.

21:54.897 --> 21:57.389
Just wanna make sure
you have my pay ready tomorrow.

21:57.817 --> 21:58.682
Yeah.

22:00.236 --> 22:01.147
Hi.

22:01.821 --> 22:02.732
Hi.

22:15.668 --> 22:17.250
You ever work with Lanny Driscoll?

22:17.795 --> 22:18.785
Lanny Driscoll?

22:19.839 --> 22:22.422
I'm a bookie. Of course I've worked with
him.

22:22.508 --> 22:24.295
What about your sister or Pierce?

22:24.385 --> 22:25.671
Do they know Lanny Driscoll?

22:25.761 --> 22:27.127
Not that I'm aware of.

22:27.221 --> 22:28.553
You think Pierce had something to do

22:28.639 --> 22:30.255
with what happened
to you and Charlie that night?

22:31.725 --> 22:32.761
Him or you.

22:36.689 --> 22:38.726
Listen, man, I don't know you well.

22:39.900 --> 22:42.608
But I knew Charlie.
We were friends, all right?

22:42.695 --> 22:44.436
I don't beat people up unless I have to.

22:44.780 --> 22:45.941
And I don't kill people.

22:46.991 --> 22:48.527
Not friends like Charlie

22:48.617 --> 22:50.859
and not scumbags like my sister's husband.

22:53.581 --> 22:54.867
What did your sister do?

22:55.249 --> 22:57.206
For work? Nothing.

22:57.459 --> 22:58.950
She painted in college.

22:59.044 --> 23:02.003
She actually started taking art classes
again over at the academy,

23:02.381 --> 23:03.588
she found out about Pierce.

23:04.300 --> 23:07.088
- What about Pierce?
- He's an accountant for the government.

23:08.053 --> 23:09.385
He never said much about it.

23:09.471 --> 23:11.337
Treasury Department, I think.

23:17.938 --> 23:19.019
That's Jen.

23:20.107 --> 23:22.019
You know, my sister,
she wasn't an important person,

23:22.109 --> 23:23.270
but she was a good person.

23:23.694 --> 23:25.356
And she deserved more than what she got.

23:25.654 --> 23:27.020
So if you find anything out,

23:27.531 --> 23:29.488
I'd appreciate it
if you let me know about it.

24:01.649 --> 24:04.562
<i>We're at the home
of government official Bill Pierce.</i>

24:04.652 --> 24:08.566
<i>This is where this morning his wife,
Jennifer Pierce, got into a car.</i>

24:08.656 --> 24:10.989
<i>There was an explosion,
and she was killed.</i>

24:11.075 --> 24:14.694
<i>Police are now investigating
the unknown cause of this explosion.</i>

24:14.787 --> 24:16.744
<i>A shock for everyone here
in the neighborhood.</i>

24:16.830 --> 24:20.995
<i>Needless to say, Bill Pierce distraught
by this turn of events.</i>

24:21.085 --> 24:21.916
<i>As you can see,</i>

24:22.002 --> 24:25.996
<i>there are emergency workers,
and investigators, explosives experts...</i>

24:50.030 --> 24:51.020
Hey, buddy?

24:51.115 --> 24:52.651
Yes, sir, what can I do for you?

24:52.741 --> 24:54.232
Jack Bagby, from up on nine.

24:54.326 --> 24:56.613
Listen, I'm a little bit embarrassed.
I'm new here.

24:56.704 --> 25:00.789
I've forgotten the name of the guy
who's talking to Bill Pierce over there.

25:00.874 --> 25:01.955
That's Mr. Loach.

25:02.418 --> 25:04.410
He's a big shot.
You don't wanna forget his name.

25:04.503 --> 25:07.041
Loach? Right! Treasury Department.

25:07.131 --> 25:08.872
Nah, Treasury's across the street.

25:08.966 --> 25:10.127
You are new here, aren't you?

25:10.718 --> 25:11.708
Yeah. Thanks, pal.

25:12.052 --> 25:12.883
Sure thing.

25:56.263 --> 25:58.380
Damn it! I've done it again,
I forgot my card.

25:58.474 --> 25:59.339
I got it.

26:00.142 --> 26:01.929
Thanks, pal. Ten, please.

26:27.419 --> 26:28.409
Can I help you?

26:29.421 --> 26:30.252
Hey, hi!

26:30.339 --> 26:32.752
Jack Bagby,
I got an appointment with Kim Masters.

26:32.841 --> 26:33.957
There's no Kim here.

26:34.426 --> 26:36.759
No Kim? 1114? Department of Interior?

26:36.845 --> 26:38.461
No, this is 1014.

26:40.224 --> 26:41.760
Oh, God, no...

26:43.018 --> 26:44.930
Great! Now I'm late. Terribly sorry.

26:45.020 --> 26:47.182
You're gonna have to go back down
and see the guard.

26:47.272 --> 26:49.810
You won't be able to get to 11
without an elevator pass.

26:49.900 --> 26:51.766
Elevator pass. Got it. Thank you.

28:21.408 --> 28:23.946
<i>There is no sin that cannot be forgiven.</i>

28:24.036 --> 28:26.323
Even when the weight of his sins

28:26.413 --> 28:30.032
has sunk the lost
deep into the lake of fire.

28:31.043 --> 28:33.000
He may be born again.

28:33.295 --> 28:34.581
So today...

28:35.422 --> 28:37.288
I ask you this question;

28:38.383 --> 28:40.466
Where will you go from here?

28:40.552 --> 28:43.670
Will you wade further
into the lake of fire,

28:44.640 --> 28:48.179
thrash among the flames
waiting to be saved?

28:48.644 --> 28:50.601
Or will you save yourself,

28:51.355 --> 28:54.018
depart from evil, and do good?

28:54.983 --> 28:56.895
For the wages of sin

28:57.611 --> 28:58.647
is death.

29:41.446 --> 29:42.937
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

30:36.376 --> 30:37.207
So...

30:37.836 --> 30:38.997
I guess I'll be going.

30:40.505 --> 30:42.337
Last night was it for me at Fatty's.

30:42.924 --> 30:43.880
I'm going home.

30:45.010 --> 30:46.000
Home's good.

30:51.350 --> 30:52.261
You know what's strange?

30:53.518 --> 30:54.929
Two years I've been here.

30:55.854 --> 30:57.937
And you're the only person
I'm saying goodbye to.

31:00.776 --> 31:01.812
I bet you got people.

31:03.320 --> 31:04.731
Somebody to say goodbye to.

31:06.323 --> 31:07.484
You'd lose.

31:20.128 --> 31:21.744
<i>Don't call again, Danny.</i>

31:27.803 --> 31:28.714
Thank you.

31:30.055 --> 31:31.262
<i>I don't know what you need.</i>

31:31.681 --> 31:33.263
<i>And I don't know how to fix it.</i>

32:31.700 --> 32:32.690
Yeah?

32:32.784 --> 32:34.901
I'm investigating the death
of Jennifer Pierce.

32:35.579 --> 32:38.538
I'm glad someone's finally
looking into what happened to Jennifer.

32:38.623 --> 32:39.830
You mind telling me about her?

32:40.167 --> 32:41.453
She was good.

32:41.543 --> 32:43.455
Little formal training,
but she had talent.

32:44.004 --> 32:45.165
Did she have any friends here,

32:45.255 --> 32:46.837
anyone she might've had
a personal connection with?

32:47.549 --> 32:48.915
Marcy Williams.

32:49.009 --> 32:50.500
Marcy Williams, who's that?

32:50.594 --> 32:51.584
I'll show you.

32:54.055 --> 32:56.138
This was Jennifer's portrait of Marcy.

32:57.225 --> 32:58.090
Beautiful.

32:58.727 --> 33:01.561
Jennifer was good, but let's face it,
she had a great subject.

33:03.690 --> 33:05.431
Would you mind showing me Marcy's records?

33:05.901 --> 33:07.483
Can't. Don't have any.

33:08.487 --> 33:09.398
What do you mean?

33:09.779 --> 33:12.066
When Jen died, I wanted to contact Marcy.

33:12.157 --> 33:13.568
